rules:

  # --------------------------------
  # ðŸ§­ Project Structure
  # --------------------------------
  - Always use semantic HTML: <header>, <main>, <section>, <footer>.
  - Use a single index.html with section-based navigation when possible.
  - For multi-page sites, use Swup.js or the Page Transition API to animate transitions smoothly.
  - Store all assets in an /assets/ directory (e.g., /assets/images/, /assets/css/, /assets/js/).
  - Maintain descriptive file and folder names for projects and images.

  # --------------------------------
  # ðŸŽ¨ Styling & Layout
  # --------------------------------
  - Default aesthetic: minimal, white or neutral background, centered content, generous whitespace.
  - Use CSS flexbox or grid for layout â€” no positioning hacks.
  - Prefer Tailwind CSS for responsive spacing and typography if included, otherwise use modular CSS.
  - Use consistent typography hierarchy: large for titles, medium for text, small for captions.
  - Include smooth CSS transitions (opacity, transform) for hovers and fades.
  - Always design mobile-first; ensure layouts are fully responsive.

  # --------------------------------
  # âš¡ Performance & Image Handling
  # --------------------------------
  - Use <img loading="lazy"> for all images to improve load performance.
  - Prefer modern image formats (WebP or AVIF) with fallbacks to JPEG.
  - Always define image aspect ratios or dimensions to avoid layout shifts.
  - Implement IntersectionObserver for lazy or delayed loading where appropriate.
  - For click-to-advance viewers, preload only the previous and next image.
  - Optimize image resolution for web; avoid loading full RAW exports.

  # --------------------------------
  # ðŸ§  JavaScript Practices
  # --------------------------------
  - Use modern ES6+ syntax (const, let, arrow functions, template literals).
  - Keep scripts modular and self-contained; one JS file per component if needed.
  - For navigation: use fade or slide transitions instead of instant DOM swaps.
  - Avoid large libraries unless essential; keep dependencies minimal.
  - Use IntersectionObserver instead of scroll event listeners for performance.
  - Include basic accessibility (keyboard navigation, alt text, focus states).

  # --------------------------------
  # ðŸª¶ Navigation
  # --------------------------------
  - The nav bar should be fixed at the top or side and minimal in design.
  - Clicking between sections should not reload the page; use JS section toggling or Swup.js.
  - Maintain consistent navigation spacing and alignment across breakpoints.
  - Use clear hover/active states with subtle transitions.

  # --------------------------------
  # ðŸ§© Components
  # --------------------------------
  - Name reusable elements descriptively (e.g., .image-viewer, .archive-grid, .nav-bar).
  - Image carousels should fade smoothly on click and preload nearby images.
  - Horizontal archives should use flexbox with overflow-x: auto and scroll-snap.
  - Support keyboard arrow navigation for carousels where possible.

  # --------------------------------
  # ðŸ§¹ Code Quality
  # --------------------------------
  - Comment all non-trivial JS functions with a short description.
  - Remove console.log() before final output.
  - Use consistent 2-space indentation.
  - Keep HTML attributes lowercase and double-quoted.
  - Include TODO comments for incomplete sections.
  - Maintain clean, minimal markup â€” avoid unnecessary wrappers.

  # --------------------------------
  # ðŸªž Accessibility & UX
  # --------------------------------
  - Include descriptive alt text for every image.
  - Ensure readable contrast between text and background.
  - Allow tab navigation for all interactive elements.
  - Avoid autoplaying or looping animations without user input.

  # --------------------------------
  # ðŸ§° Optional Enhancements
  # --------------------------------
  - Use blur-up placeholders for lazy-loaded images when practical.
  - Apply subtle fade-in animations on image load.
  - Implement a simple lightbox for viewing images fullscreen.
  - If using Swup.js, define a .transition-fade class for consistent cross-page animation.

